        url: "https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/business/real-estate/2026/04/16/canadian-housing-market-sees-prices-dip-in-big-cities-while-market-booms-in-others-royal-lepage/",
        summary: "Canada's housing market is experiencing divergent trends, with mid-sized cities like Quebec City seeing price increases of over 10 percent while major markets such as Toronto and Vancouver experienced declines of roughly 4.5 percent or more year-over-year, according to Royal LePage's first-quarter data. The split is attributed to tight inventory in smaller regions, changing buyer behavior, and oversupply in urban condo markets, though overall Canadian home prices fell 2 percent annually to an average of $812,900.",
