        primaryBeneficiary: "Seniors",
        storyBlurb: "Denver and its development partners broke ground on Iliff Apartments, a new 50-unit affordable housing community dedicated to adults aged 62 and older in the University Hills neighborhood. The project addresses a recognized shortage of affordable senior housing in Denver, where older adults on fixed incomes face acute affordability pressures in an increasingly expensive housing market.\n\nIliff Apartments will provide income-restricted rental homes specifically designed to meet the physical and social needs of older residents, including accessibility features and proximity to neighborhood amenities. The University Hills location offers seniors access to transit, retail, and community services, supporting aging in place in a walkable urban environment.\n\nThe project is backed by Denver's Department of Housing Stability and financed through a combination of affordable housing tax credits and public subsidies. It represents one component of Denver's broader strategy of targeting housing investments toward populations with acute needs, including seniors, who face compounding vulnerabilities from fixed incomes, healthcare costs, and the rising cost of housing in Colorado's largest city.",
